OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1774368667
OL,3,CLast-remaining puffin colony in Dorset
OL,4,Ccould 'die out'
OL,6,FThe last remaining colony of puffins
OL,7,Fon the South coast could 'die out' if
OL,8,Fthe birds fail to produce chicks in
OL,9,Fthe coming years.
OL,11,FAround forty pairs of puffins used to
OL,12,Fnest on the South coast 80 years ago,
OL,13,Fbut the population has plummeted to
OL,14,Fjust three pairs on the cliffs near
OL,15,FDancing Ledge in Purbeck. They are now
OL,16,Famong the rarest breeding birds in
OL,17,FDorset.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
