PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1774368667
OL,3,CLast-remaining puffin colony in Dorset
OL,4,Ccould 'die out'
OL,6,FIn a last-ditch attempt to save the
OL,7,Fcolony, the National Trust is
OL,8,Finstalling cameras across the cliffs
OL,9,Fto try and work out why the puffins'
OL,10,Fchicks aren't surviving to adulthood.
OL,12,FMotion-sensor trail cameras were
OL,13,Finstalled by high ropes experts to
OL,14,Fcapture footage of the puffins at
OL,15,Ftheir breeding site.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1774368667
OL,3,CLast-remaining puffin colony in Dorset
OL,4,Ccould 'die out'
OL,6,FBen Cooke, Rivers and Coast project
OL,7,Fofficer for the National Trust in
OL,8,FPurbeck, said: "Our puffins are
OL,9,Falready under threat. With the colony
OL,10,Fbeing so small we fear that even if
OL,11,Fjust one of the Purbeck birds were
OL,12,Flost to the storms this winter, it
OL,13,Fwould be another step closer to the
OL,14,Floss of the whole colony."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1774368667
OL,3,CLast-remaining puffin colony in Dorset
OL,4,Ccould 'die out'
OL,6,FHe added: "The puffins spend the
OL,7,Fwinter far out at sea, returning to
OL,8,Ftheir nesting sites in late March. So
OL,9,Ffar we've had reports that four of the
OL,10,Fpuffins have made it back - we are
OL,11,Fwaiting with some trepidation to see
OL,12,Fif the other two make it."
OL,14,FSpecialist teams have been abseiling
OL,15,Fdown the cliffs to install new solar-
OL,16,Fpowered cameras near the breeding
OL,17,Fsites.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1774368667
OL,3,CLast-remaining puffin colony in Dorset
OL,4,Ccould 'die out'
OL,6,FResearchers at the National Trust
OL,7,Fsuspect that the colony's eggs and
OL,8,Fchicks are being preyed upon by rats
OL,9,Fand crows. The hope is that the
OL,10,Fcameras will help identify the animals
OL,11,Fpreying on the puffins so the
OL,12,Fresearchers can find new ways to
OL,13,Fprotect the colony.
OL,15,FLed by Dr Richard Caldow, a marine
OL,16,Fornithologist, the project is the next
OL,17,Fphase in an initiative which was first
OL,18,Frolled out in 2024 when cameras
OL,19,Fcaptured the puffins' behaviour
OL,20,Fthroughout the nesting season.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1774368667
OL,3,CLast-remaining puffin colony in Dorset
OL,4,Ccould 'die out'
OL,6,FDr Caldow said: "If we are to do
OL,7,Fanything to help this puffin colony to
OL,8,Fsurvive, we need to establish what is
OL,9,Fgoing wrong. Puffins were once
OL,10,Fabundant on this coastline ` with some
OL,11,F85 birds recorded in Purbeck in 1958.
OL,12,FThe colony has now plummeted to just
OL,13,Fthree pairs.
OL,15,F"Adult puffins typically have a high
OL,16,Fannual survival rate so can live for a
OL,17,Flong time, but eventually they will
OL,18,Fdie and if they don't breed
OL,19,Fsuccessfully enough to replace
OL,20,Fthemselves, a colony is very likely to
OL,21,Fdwindle and perhaps die too."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1774368667
OL,3,CLast-remaining puffin colony in Dorset
OL,4,Ccould 'die out'
OL,6,FFears for the future of the species
OL,7,Fhave grown after reports that
OL,8,Fthousands of dead puffins washed
OL,9,Fashore on beaches across Europe during
OL,10,Fstorms this winter.
OL,12,FHowever, there are some positive signs
OL,13,Ffor the puffins. Stocks of small fish
OL,14,F- including sardines, sprats and
OL,15,Fanchovies - which the colony eat have
OL,16,Fbeen plentiful, according to Dr Caldow.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1774368667
OL,3,CLast-remaining puffin colony in Dorset
OL,4,Ccould 'die out'
OL,6,F"It seems unlikely that a lack of fish
OL,7,Fhas been the puffins' problem," he
OL,8,Fsaid. "Our suspicion has long been
OL,9,Fthat predators such as rats or crows
OL,10,Fare taking the puffin eggs or chicks."
OL,12,FThe last time the cameras were
OL,13,Finstalled, a team of volunteers combed
OL,14,Fthrough more than 70,000 images but
OL,15,Ffound no evidence for why the puffin
OL,16,Fchicks seemed to be dying prematurely.
OL,17,FThis time round, the researchers
OL,18,Fbelieve they should get better footage
OL,19,Fand a clearer picture of what's
OL,20,Fhappening to the colony.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G8/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
